name: Hawthorne Ridge
description:
ABOUT THE HOME ENERGY RATING SCALE
The HERS (Home Energy Rating System) Index allows buyers to compare the relative energy efficiency of different homes. The HERS Index home energy rating is determined by an independent RESNET-certified home energy rater ("Rater"). The lower a home’s score, the more energy efficient it is in comparison to the HERS referenced home. For every one-point decrease in the HERS Index score, there is a corresponding one percent (1%) reduction in energy consumption as compared to a home with a HERS Index of 100. A home with a HERS score of 100 reflects a home built to 2006 IEEC Building Codes. See the bottom of this page for more information on HERS scores.

amenities.name: Home Designs
amenities.description: Pulte Homes brings affordably priced new construction homes for sale in Henry County at McDonough’s Hawthorne Ridge

amenities.name: Home Designs
amenities.description: Homesites feature spacious, flat backyards while interiors showcase More Life Built In Home Designs from one of the nation’s best home builders

amenities.name: Planned amenities
amenities.description: Planned amenities to feature a community pool, 1,800 square foot clubhouse, dog park, and fire pit

amenities.name: Just 4-minute
amenities.description: Just a 4-minute drive to Interstate 75 – with direct commuting access north into Stockbridge and Atlanta or south to Locust Grove

amenities.name: Square Footage
amenities.description: McDonough Square is just 5 miles from Hawthorne Ridge – offering opportunities to eat, shop, play and stay within a thriving downtown area that offers local eateries like Holy Smokes and Gritz, friendly shops and an exciting calendar of events that includes holiday celebrations, live music and the famed Geranium Festival

amenities.name: Home Designs
amenities.description: Within 1.5-mile drive of Henry Town Center with numerous retail and dining options including Target, Home Depot, Chili’s and Old Navy

amenities.name: Just miles
amenities.description: Just 5 miles away, Hudson Bridge offers a wealth of conveniences such as grocery shopping at Publix, Kroger or Walmart and dining at Chick-Fil-A, Zaxby’s or Mellow Mushroom

amenities.name: Within 3-mile
amenities.description: Within a 3-mile drive of South Point Center with several recognizable national brands like TJ Maxx, Chipotle, Rooms to Go, Panera, Hobby Lobby and more

amenities.name: Additional shops
amenities.description: Additional shops and restaurants can be found at Lake Dow Shoppes (6.5 mi) and Tanger Outlets at Locust Grove (10.5 mi)

amenities.name: Recreational opportunities
amenities.description: Recreational opportunities abound at nearby North Mt Carmel Park, Heritage Park and Georgia National Country Club

amenities.name: Nearby Southern
amenities.description: Nearby Southern Belle Farm offers a year-round country market and seasonal events like berry picking in the spring and summer, corn maze and pumpkin patch in the fall and Christmas trees in the winter

amenities.name: Convenient Downtown
amenities.description: Convenient to Downtown Atlanta and several of Henry County’s top employers, including Henry County Schools, Luxottica Retail Group, Piedmont Henry Hospital, Henry County Government and Federal Aviation Administration

amenities.name: Gigabit Internet
amenities.description: Gigabit Internet is included in the HOA fees
